## When to use this template

Only when none of the prebuilt scenarios match:

- ✅ Use this for: a novel one-off scenario
- ❌ Don't use this for: scenarios that already have templates (proposal cover, AR follow-up, etc.) — use those instead

## After drafting

If the new scenario is something you'll encounter again, **promote it to a named template** in `templates/` so future drafts inherit the structure:

1. Save the draft as `templates/<new-scenario-slug>.md.template`
2. Generalize the customer-specific values into `{{PLACEHOLDER}}` tokens
3. Add a "When to use this template" section
4. Add an "Operator review checklist" section
5. Update `SKILL.md`'s scenario-keyword table to route future requests to the new template

This is how the template library grows — every novel email becomes a reusable asset.

